[requests] anchor trace context to child span in requests wrapper

commit.message:
[requests] anchor trace context to child span in requests wrapper

Found this when writing the blog post a few weeks back. Here's an example trace with the bug: https://ui.honeycomb.io/honeycomb-internal/datasets/travis.python-testing/result/62pS9eAnAXs/trace/tauLSpNhojm

The "todo-app" spans should be children of the "requests_get" span.

I tweaked all of the global API functions to use `get_beeline` rather than the `_GBL` (global beeline) variable to make test patching cleaner and more consistent. Also, apparently we weren't running middleware tests because they weren't in the `test_suite` module. Oops.

Merge pull request #97 from honeycombio/tredman.bump

Add type safety checking in add_trace_field, bump version

commit.message:
Add type safety checking in add_trace_field, bump version

https://github.com/honeycombio/beeline-python/pull/96 added a string content check to the trace field name, but there were previously no checks to ensure that this value is in fact a string. Any customer using the beeline that picks up that patch and is using unusual types here could crash, so I added some type checking before bumping the version on this release.
